  "instructions": "<p>Inside the quarter, go up the mountain ([map c=\"32711,31175,7\" map]here[/map]) and down to the center area ([map c=\"32688,31124,6\" map]here[/map]).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Good respawn for premium account knights who want to rush experience and don't care for waste. You can start here at level 100 with minimum skills 85/85+.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The spawn is small and can only accomodate one player. If there is another person hunting here, don't waste your time because both experience and loot will be bad.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>It's a better spawn for knights than the Cemitery Quarter because each floor is small and when Nightmares run you can reach them without luring more monsters.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>‚öîÔ∏è <strong>Strategy</strong></p>\n<p>It's a dangerous place for this range of level. Don't be fooled into thinking that the location is easy due to the low number of monsters. Two nightmares can do a lot of damage and send you back to the temple if you don't watch out.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Go down the floors shown in the video and use the map to your advantage (dodging from monsters by going to the edges).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>‚ö†Ô∏è Be careful not to go down floors which you don't know yet because you may find destroyers, plaguesmiths and even a demon ‚ö†Ô∏è&nbsp;</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>If you have to use health potions, use mercilessly.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üíØ <strong>Experience</strong></p>\n<p>One can make 300k to 400k of experience per hour (up to 600k/h on green stamina).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üí∏ <strong>Loot</strong></p>\n<p>Altought there is a chance to drop valuable items (like BOH), it's rare and usually you'll have waste.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üêª <strong>Task</strong></p>\n<p>Nightmares are <a href=\"https://tibia.fandom.com/wiki/Killing_in_the_Name_of..._Quest/Spoiler#Nightmares\">taskable</a> between levels 80-129. You must kill 400 nightmares or nightmare scions and after that you can kill the boss (pretty far though, on Svargrond mines).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The task can (and should) be repeated if you are willing to waste some gold.</p>",
